			const backtotop_button = document.querySelector(".backtotop");
			const scrollAmount = 100; // number of px before Back to Top button shows.

			window.onscroll = function() {
				// handles when user scrolls more than scrollAmount, then we show the Back to Top button
				if (document.body.scrollTop > scrollAmount || document.documentElement.scrollTop > scrollAmount) {
					backtotop_button.setAttribute('show', 'true');
				} 
				// handles when user has not scrolled at all (i.e. on page load)
				else if (document.body.scrollTop <= scrollAmount && !backtotop_button.hasAttribute('show')) {
					return
				} 
				// handles when user scrolls down and then back up, 
				// or has scrolled down and then clicks the Back to Top button
				else {
					backtotop_button.setAttribute('show', 'false');
				}
			}
		});</script></footer><script type="speculationrules">

<style id="bricks-global-classes-inline-inline-css">

/* BREAKPOINT: Desktop (BASE) */
.page__breadcrumb-section {padding-top: 16px; padding-bottom: 16px; background-color: #000000}


/* BREAKPOINT: Desktop (BASE) */
.page__breadcrumb-text {color: var(--bricks-color-nwurdf); font-family: "dunbar-tall"}
.page__breadcrumb-text .item[aria-current="page"] {text-decoration: none}
.page__breadcrumb-text .item { text-decoration: underline;}


/* BREAKPOINT: Desktop (BASE) */
.page__hero-section {position: relative; padding-top: 120px; padding-bottom: 120px}
:where(.page__hero-section > *) {position: relative}
.page__hero-section::before {background-image: linear-gradient(90deg, #000000 20%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)); position: absolute; content: ""; top: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0; left: 0; pointer-events: none}
.page__hero-section::before { z-index: 0 !important;}

/* BREAKPOINT: Mobile landscape */
@media (max-width: 767px) {
.page__hero-section {padding-top: 60px; padding-bottom: 60px; position: relative}
:where(.page__hero-section > *) {position: relative}
.page__hero-section::before {background-image: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8) 30%, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3)); position: absolute; content: ""; top: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0; left: 0; pointer-events: none}
}

/* BREAKPOINT: Desktop (BASE) */
.page__hero-bg {position: absolute; top: 0px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; left: 20%; width: 80%; height: 100%; z-index: -1}
.page__hero-bg:not(.tag), .page__hero-bg img {object-fit: cover}

/* BREAKPOINT: Mobile landscape */
@media (max-width: 767px) {
.page__hero-bg {left: 0px; width: 100%}
.page__hero-bg:not(.tag), .page__hero-bg img {object-position: 100% 50%}
}

/* BREAKPOINT: Desktop (BASE) */
.page__hero-overlay {position: absolute; top: 0px; bottom: 0px; right: 0px; left: 0px; opacity: 0.4; pointer-events: none}


/* BREAKPOINT: Desktop (BASE) */
.page__hero-container {flex-direction: row}


/* BREAKPOINT: Desktop (BASE) */
.page__hero-content-left {width: 1000px; z-index: 1}


/* BREAKPOINT: Desktop (BASE) */
.page__hero-title {color: var(--bricks-color-nwurdf); text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 400}

/* BREAKPOINT: Mobile landscape */
@media (max-width: 767px) {
.page__hero-title {align-self: flex-start}
}

/* BREAKPOINT: Desktop (BASE) */
.page__hero-tagline {color: var(--bricks-color-nwurdf); font-size: 3em; margin-bottom: 24px}
.page__hero-tagline br {  content: "\a";  display: block;  height: 0.5em;}

/* BREAKPOINT: Mobile landscape */
@media (max-width: 767px) {
.page__hero-tagline {font-size: 2.5em}
}
/* BREAKPOINT: Mobile portrait */
@media (max-width: 478px) {
.page__hero-tagline {font-size: 2.25em}
}

/* BREAKPOINT: Desktop (BASE) */
.page__hero-content-right {width: fit-content}


</style>
